        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[How I Passed the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer Exam]]></title>
            <link>https://souravgke052-coder.github.io/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips</link>
            <guid>https://souravgke052-coder.github.io/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips</guid>
            <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jun 2025 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Study tips, resources, and hands-on strategies for passing the GCP Associate Cloud Engineer certification.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Passing the <strong>Google Cloud Associate Cloud Engineer</strong> exam requires a mix of hands-on practice and focused study. Here are the strategies that worked for me.</p>
<!-- -->
<hr>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="study-resources">Study Resources<a href="https://souravgke052-coder.github.io/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips#study-resources" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Study Resources" title="Direct link to Study Resources" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong>Official Google Cloud documentation</strong> — read it like a textbook</li>
<li class=""><strong>Google Cloud Skills Boost</strong> — Quest: "Prepare for Your Associate Cloud Engineer Journey"</li>
<li class=""><strong>Practice exams</strong> — Linux Academy / A Cloud Guru / Coursera</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="key-focus-areas">Key Focus Areas<a href="https://souravgke052-coder.github.io/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips#key-focus-areas" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Key Focus Areas" title="Direct link to Key Focus Areas" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ol>
<li class="">
<p><strong>IAM &amp; Identity</strong></p>
<ul>
<li class="">Understand the difference between primitive, predefined, and custom roles</li>
<li class="">Know when to use Service Accounts vs User Accounts</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Compute Engines</strong></p>
<ul>
<li class="">Know how to create and manage GCE instances</li>
<li class="">Understand startup scripts and metadata</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Kubernetes Engine (GKE)</strong></p>
<ul>
<li class="">Deploy clusters using Console and <code>gcloud</code></li>
<li class="">Know basic <code>kubectl</code> commands</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="">
<p><strong>Storage &amp; Databases</strong></p>
<ul>
<li class="">Cloud Storage bucket classes and use cases</li>
<li class="">When to use Cloud SQL vs Cloud Spanner vs BigQuery</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="hands-on-practice">Hands-On Practice<a href="https://souravgke052-coder.github.io/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips#hands-on-practice" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Hands-On Practice" title="Direct link to Hands-On Practice" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Create a mini project: deploy a VM, attach a persistent disk, configure a firewall rule, and host a simple app.</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#393A34;--prism-background-color:#f6f8fa"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#393A34;background-color:#f6f8fa"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">gcloud compute instances create web-server </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">\</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  --image-family</span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">=</span><span class="token plain">debian-11 </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">\</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  --image-project</span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">=</span><span class="token plain">debian-cloud </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">\</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  --machine-type</span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">=</span><span class="token plain">e2-micro </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">\</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token parameter variable" style="color:#36acaa">--zone</span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">=</span><span class="token plain">us-central1-a </span><span class="token punctuation" style="color:#393A34">\</span><span class="token plain"></span><br></div><div class="token-line" style="color:#393A34"><span class="token plain">  </span><span class="token parameter variable" style="color:#36acaa">--tags</span><span class="token operator" style="color:#393A34">=</span><span class="token plain">http-server</span><br></div></code></pre></div></div>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="exam-day-tips">Exam Day Tips<a href="https://souravgke052-coder.github.io/devops-blog/blog/gcp-associate-exam-tips#exam-day-tips" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Exam Day Tips" title="Direct link to Exam Day Tips" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li class="">Flag uncertain questions and return later</li>
<li class="">Know the pricing model basics (sustained use discounts, committed use)</li>
<li class="">Time management: 2 hours for 50 questions</li>
</ul>
<p>Good luck!</p>]]></content:encoded>
